{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":745,"text":"To give me an idea of how many of you here"},{"time":2974,"text":"may find what I'm about to tell you"},{"time":5096,"text":"of practical value,"},{"time":6721,"text":"let me ask you please to raise your hands:"},{"time":9410,"text":"Who here is either over 65 years old"},{"time":12977,"text":"or hopes to live past age 65"},{"time":16746,"text":"or has parents or grandparents who did live"},{"time":19691,"text":"or have lived past 65,"},{"time":21658,"text":"raise your hands please. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":24243,"text":"Okay. You are the people to whom my talk"},{"time":26397,"text":"will be of practical value. (Laughter)"},{"time":28831,"text":"The rest of you"},{"time":30488,"text":"won't find my talk personally relevant,"},{"time":32276,"text":"but I think that you will still find the subject"},{"time":34190,"text":"fascinating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35837,"text":"I'm going to talk about growing older"},{"time":37469,"text":"in traditional societies."},{"time":39888,"text":"This subject constitutes just one chapter"},{"time":42634,"text":"of my latest book, which compares"},{"time":45225,"text":"traditional, small, tribal societies"},{"time":48442,"text":"with our large, modern societies,"},{"time":50992,"text":"with respect to many topics"},{"time":52617,"text":"such as bringing up children,"},{"time":54476,"text":"growing older, health, dealing with danger,"},{"time":58397,"text":"settling disputes, religion"},{"time":60742,"text":"and speaking more than one language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63533,"text":"Those tribal societies, which constituted"},{"time":66090,"text":"all human societies for most of human history,"},{"time":69075,"text":"are far more diverse than are our modern,"},{"time":72369,"text":"recent, big societies."},{"time":74536,"text":"All big societies that have governments,"},{"time":76899,"text":"and where most people are strangers to each other,"},{"time":79165,"text":"are inevitably similar to each other"},{"time":81513,"text":"and different from tribal societies."},{"time":84361,"text":"Tribes constitute thousands of natural experiments"},{"time":87672,"text":"in how to run a human society."},{"time":90221,"text":"They constitute experiments from which we ourselves"},{"time":93028,"text":"may be able to learn."},{"time":95430,"text":"Tribal societies shouldn't be scorned"},{"time":97450,"text":"as primitive and miserable,"},{"time":99186,"text":"but also they shouldn't be romanticized"},{"time":101557,"text":"as happy and peaceful."},{"time":103774,"text":"When we learn of tribal practices,"},{"time":106033,"text":"some of them will horrify us,"},{"time":107807,"text":"but there are other tribal practices which,"},{"time":110357,"text":"when we hear about them,"},{"time":111706,"text":"we may admire and envy"},{"time":113653,"text":"and wonder whether we could adopt those practices"},{"time":115877,"text":"ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118574,"text":"Most old people in the U.S. end up living"},{"time":121661,"text":"separately from their children"},{"time":123648,"text":"and from most of their friends"},{"time":125154,"text":"of their earlier years,"},{"time":126846,"text":"and often they live in separate\nretirements homes for the elderly,"},{"time":130700,"text":"whereas in traditional societies,"},{"time":132908,"text":"older people instead live out their lives"},{"time":135742,"text":"among their children, their other relatives,"},{"time":137908,"text":"and their lifelong friends."},{"time":140305,"text":"Nevertheless, the treatment of the elderly"},{"time":142474,"text":"varies enormously among traditional societies,"},{"time":145639,"text":"from much worse to much better"},{"time":147820,"text":"than in our modern societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150778,"text":"At the worst extreme, many traditional societies"},{"time":153575,"text":"get rid of their elderly"},{"time":155388,"text":"in one of four increasingly direct ways:"},{"time":158919,"text":"by neglecting their elderly"},{"time":160582,"text":"and not feeding or cleaning them until they die,"},{"time":164011,"text":"or by abandoning them when the group moves,"},{"time":167065,"text":"or by encouraging older people to commit suicide,"},{"time":170204,"text":"or by killing older people."},{"time":173249,"text":"In which tribal societies do children"},{"time":175998,"text":"abandon or kill their parents?"},{"time":178384,"text":"It happens mainly under two conditions."},{"time":181408,"text":"One is in nomadic, hunter-gather societies"},{"time":184388,"text":"that often shift camp"},{"time":186111,"text":"and that are physically incapable"},{"time":188290,"text":"of transporting old people who can't walk"},{"time":191413,"text":"when the able-bodied younger people already"},{"time":193973,"text":"have to carry their young children"},{"time":195908,"text":"and all their physical possessions."},{"time":198726,"text":"The other condition is in societies"},{"time":200890,"text":"living in marginal or fluctuating environments,"},{"time":204200,"text":"such as the Arctic or deserts,"},{"time":206533,"text":"where there are periodic food shortages,"},{"time":209117,"text":"and occasionally there just isn't enough food"},{"time":211046,"text":"to keep everyone alive."},{"time":213526,"text":"Whatever food is available has to be reserved"},{"time":215950,"text":"for able-bodied adults and for children."},{"time":220275,"text":"To us Americans, it sounds horrible"},{"time":223175,"text":"to think of abandoning or killing"},{"time":225408,"text":"your own sick wife or husband"},{"time":227589,"text":"or elderly mother or father,"},{"time":229888,"text":"but what could those traditional societies"},{"time":233647,"text":"do differently?"},{"time":235130,"text":"They face a cruel situation of no choice."},{"time":238950,"text":"Their old people had to do it to their own parents,"},{"time":241945,"text":"and the old people know"},{"time":243233,"text":"what now is going to happen to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246384,"text":"At the opposite extreme"},{"time":248198,"text":"in treatment of the elderly, the happy extreme,"},{"time":250877,"text":"are the New Guinea farming societies"},{"time":252864,"text":"where I've been doing my fieldwork \nfor the past 50 years,"},{"time":255861,"text":"and most other sedentary traditional societies"},{"time":259108,"text":"around the world."},{"time":261194,"text":"In those societies, older people are cared for."},{"time":264142,"text":"They are fed. They remain valuable."},{"time":266492,"text":"And they continue to live in the same hut"},{"time":268680,"text":"or else in a nearby hut near their children,"},{"time":271367,"text":"relatives and lifelong friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275266,"text":"There are two main sets of reasons for this variation"},{"time":277698,"text":"among societies in their treatment"},{"time":280053,"text":"of old people."},{"time":281450,"text":"The variation depends especially"},{"time":283087,"text":"on the usefulness of old people"},{"time":285357,"text":"and on the society's values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288070,"text":"First, as regards usefulness,"},{"time":290393,"text":"older people continue to perform useful services."},{"time":293848,"text":"One use of older people in traditional societies"},{"time":296533,"text":"is that they often are still effective"},{"time":298533,"text":"at producing food."},{"time":300946,"text":"Another traditional usefulness of older people"},{"time":303359,"text":"is that they are capable of babysitting"},{"time":306638,"text":"their grandchildren,"},{"time":308332,"text":"thereby freeing up their own adult children,"},{"time":311002,"text":"the parents of those grandchildren,"},{"time":312873,"text":"to go hunting and gathering\nfood for the grandchildren."},{"time":316346,"text":"Still another traditional value of older people"},{"time":318551,"text":"is in making tools, weapons, baskets,"},{"time":321471,"text":"pots and textiles."},{"time":323428,"text":"In fact, they're usually the people who are best at it."},{"time":326677,"text":"Older people usually are the leaders"},{"time":329445,"text":"of traditional societies,"},{"time":331294,"text":"and the people most knowledgeable about politics,"},{"time":334553,"text":"medicine, religion, songs and dances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338552,"text":"Finally, older people in traditional societies"},{"time":341004,"text":"have a huge significance that would never occur"},{"time":344931,"text":"to us in our modern, literate societies,"},{"time":348607,"text":"where our sources of information are books"},{"time":351022,"text":"and the Internet."},{"time":352706,"text":"In contrast, in traditional societies without writing,"},{"time":356129,"text":"older people are the repositories of information."},{"time":359815,"text":"It's their knowledge that spells the difference"},{"time":362380,"text":"between survival and death for their whole society"},{"time":366130,"text":"in a time of crisis caused by rare events"},{"time":369388,"text":"for which only the oldest people alive"},{"time":371983,"text":"have had experience."},{"time":374272,"text":"Those, then, are the ways in which older people"},{"time":376742,"text":"are useful in traditional societies."},{"time":379645,"text":"Their usefulness varies and contributes"},{"time":382207,"text":"to variation in the society's treatment"},{"time":384825,"text":"of the elderly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386825,"text":"The other set of reasons for variation"},{"time":388644,"text":"in the treatment of the elderly is"},{"time":390519,"text":"the society's cultural values."},{"time":393754,"text":"For example, there's particular emphasis"},{"time":395780,"text":"on respect for the elderly in East Asia,"},{"time":398989,"text":"associated with Confucius' doctrine"},{"time":401900,"text":"of filial piety, which means obedience,"},{"time":405450,"text":"respect and support for elderly parents."},{"time":409544,"text":"Cultural values that emphasize\nrespect for older people"},{"time":413257,"text":"contrast with the low status of the elderly"},{"time":416074,"text":"in the U.S."},{"time":418236,"text":"Older Americans are at a big disadvantage"},{"time":420794,"text":"in job applications."},{"time":422907,"text":"They're at a big disadvantage in hospitals."},{"time":425442,"text":"Our hospitals have an explicit policy"},{"time":428065,"text":"called age-based allocation of healthcare resources."},{"time":433032,"text":"That sinister expression means that"},{"time":435805,"text":"if hospital resources are limited,"},{"time":438011,"text":"for example if only one donor heart"},{"time":440061,"text":"becomes available for transplant,"},{"time":442359,"text":"or if a surgeon has time to operate"},{"time":444461,"text":"on only a certain number of patients,"},{"time":446972,"text":"American hospitals have an explicit policy"},{"time":449922,"text":"of giving preference to younger patients"},{"time":452242,"text":"over older patients"},{"time":453722,"text":"on the grounds that younger patients are considered"},{"time":456966,"text":"more valuable to society"},{"time":458783,"text":"because they have more years of life ahead of them,"},{"time":461428,"text":"even though the younger patients have fewer years"},{"time":464088,"text":"of valuable life experience behind them."},{"time":468070,"text":"There are several reasons for this low status"},{"time":470298,"text":"of the elderly in the U.S."},{"time":472640,"text":"One is our Protestant work ethic"},{"time":475825,"text":"which places high value on work,"},{"time":478138,"text":"so older people who are no longer working"},{"time":480361,"text":"aren't respected."},{"time":482344,"text":"Another reason is our American emphasis"},{"time":485201,"text":"on the virtues of self-reliance and independence,"},{"time":488584,"text":"so we instinctively look down on older people"},{"time":491653,"text":"who are no longer self-reliant and independent."},{"time":495250,"text":"Still a third reason is our American cult of youth,"},{"time":499351,"text":"which shows up even in our advertisements."},{"time":502159,"text":"Ads for Coca-Cola and beer always depict"},{"time":505423,"text":"smiling young people,"},{"time":506978,"text":"even though old as well as young people"},{"time":508948,"text":"buy and drink Coca-Cola and beer."},{"time":511270,"text":"Just think, what's the last time you saw"},{"time":513273,"text":"a Coke or beer ad depicting smiling people"},{"time":515950,"text":"85 years old? Never."},{"time":518899,"text":"Instead, the only American ads"},{"time":520705,"text":"featuring white-haired old people"},{"time":522711,"text":"are ads for retirement homes and pension planning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526576,"text":"Well, what has changed in the status"},{"time":528626,"text":"of the elderly today"},{"time":530609,"text":"compared to their status in traditional societies?"},{"time":533998,"text":"There have been a few changes for the better"},{"time":535868,"text":"and more changes for the worse."},{"time":538073,"text":"Big changes for the better"},{"time":539674,"text":"include the fact that today we enjoy"},{"time":541825,"text":"much longer lives,"},{"time":543809,"text":"much better health in our old age,"},{"time":546103,"text":"and much better recreational opportunities."},{"time":549741,"text":"Another change for the better is that we now have"},{"time":552011,"text":"specialized retirement facilities"},{"time":554851,"text":"and programs to take care of old people."},{"time":558202,"text":"Changes for the worse begin with the cruel reality"},{"time":561070,"text":"that we now have"},{"time":562759,"text":"more old people and fewer young people"},{"time":565333,"text":"than at any time in the past."},{"time":568017,"text":"That means that all those old people"},{"time":569768,"text":"are more of a burden on the few young people,"},{"time":572193,"text":"and that each old person has less individual value."},{"time":576679,"text":"Another big change for the worse\nin the status of the elderly"},{"time":579863,"text":"is the breaking of social ties with age,"},{"time":582540,"text":"because older people, their children,"},{"time":584384,"text":"and their friends,"},{"time":585700,"text":"all move and scatter independently of each other"},{"time":588550,"text":"many times during their lives."},{"time":590804,"text":"We Americans move on the average"},{"time":592617,"text":"every five years."},{"time":594570,"text":"Hence our older people are likely"},{"time":596601,"text":"to end up living distant from their children"},{"time":598908,"text":"and the friends of their youth."},{"time":601711,"text":"Yet another change for the worse\nin the status of the elderly"},{"time":604873,"text":"is formal retirement from the workforce,"},{"time":608603,"text":"carrying with it a loss of work friendships"},{"time":611353,"text":"and a loss of the self-esteem associated with work."},{"time":615493,"text":"Perhaps the biggest change for the worse"},{"time":617978,"text":"is that our elderly are objectively"},{"time":620851,"text":"less useful than in traditional societies."},{"time":624013,"text":"Widespread literacy means that they are no longer"},{"time":626976,"text":"useful as repositories of knowledge."},{"time":629607,"text":"When we want some information,"},{"time":631550,"text":"we look it up in a book or we Google it"},{"time":633811,"text":"instead of finding some old person to ask."},{"time":637281,"text":"The slow pace of technological change"},{"time":639368,"text":"in traditional societies"},{"time":641190,"text":"means that what someone learns there as a child"},{"time":644040,"text":"is still useful when that person is old,"},{"time":646699,"text":"but the rapid pace of technological change today"},{"time":650302,"text":"means that what we learn as children"},{"time":652369,"text":"is no longer useful 60 years later."},{"time":655259,"text":"And conversely, we older people are not fluent"},{"time":657638,"text":"in the technologies essential for surviving"},{"time":660672,"text":"in modern society."},{"time":662643,"text":"For example, as a 15-year-old,"},{"time":664816,"text":"I was considered outstandingly\ngood at multiplying numbers"},{"time":668406,"text":"because I had memorized the multiplication tables"},{"time":671601,"text":"and I know how to use logarithms"},{"time":673746,"text":"and I'm quick at manipulating a slide rule."},{"time":676609,"text":"Today, though, those skills are utterly useless"},{"time":679695,"text":"because any idiot"},{"time":682066,"text":"can now multiply eight-digit numbers"},{"time":684424,"text":"accurately and instantly with a pocket calculator."},{"time":687611,"text":"Conversely, I at age 75"},{"time":689781,"text":"am incompetent at skills"},{"time":692445,"text":"essential for everyday life."},{"time":694899,"text":"My family's first TV set in 1948"},{"time":697683,"text":"had only three knobs that I quickly mastered:"},{"time":700736,"text":"an on-off switch, a volume knob,"},{"time":703486,"text":"and a channel selector knob."},{"time":705707,"text":"Today, just to watch a program"},{"time":707795,"text":"on the TV set in my own house,"},{"time":710251,"text":"I have to operate a 41-button TV remote"},{"time":713968,"text":"that utterly defeats me."},{"time":715950,"text":"I have to telephone my 25-year-old sons"},{"time":718964,"text":"and ask them to talk me through it"},{"time":721161,"text":"while I try to push those wretched 41 buttons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726158,"text":"What can we do to improve the lives of the elderly"},{"time":728805,"text":"in the U.S., and to make better use of their value?"},{"time":732259,"text":"That's a huge problem."},{"time":734033,"text":"In my remaining four minutes today,"},{"time":736504,"text":"I can offer just a few suggestions."},{"time":739081,"text":"One value of older people is that they are"},{"time":741003,"text":"increasingly useful as grandparents"},{"time":744447,"text":"for offering high-quality childcare"},{"time":746954,"text":"to their grandchildren, if they choose to do it,"},{"time":749607,"text":"as more young women enter the workforce"},{"time":752456,"text":"and as fewer young parents of either gender"},{"time":754790,"text":"stay home as full-time caretakers of their children."},{"time":758450,"text":"Compared to the usual alternatives"},{"time":760486,"text":"of paid babysitters and day care centers,"},{"time":764084,"text":"grandparents offer superior, motivated,"},{"time":767211,"text":"experienced child care."},{"time":769899,"text":"They've already gained experience\nfrom raising their own children."},{"time":773165,"text":"They usually love their grandchildren,"},{"time":775509,"text":"and are eager to spend time with them."},{"time":778174,"text":"Unlike other caregivers,"},{"time":780075,"text":"grandparents don't quit their job"},{"time":782972,"text":"because they found another job with higher pay"},{"time":785408,"text":"looking after another baby."},{"time":788921,"text":"A second value of older people is paradoxically"},{"time":791325,"text":"related to their loss of value"},{"time":793986,"text":"as a result of changing world\nconditions and technology."},{"time":798059,"text":"At the same time, older people have gained"},{"time":800095,"text":"in value today precisely because"},{"time":802406,"text":"of their unique experience of living conditions"},{"time":805515,"text":"that have now become rare"},{"time":807234,"text":"because of rapid change, but that could come back."},{"time":810544,"text":"For example, only Americans now in their 70s"},{"time":813498,"text":"or older today can remember"},{"time":815758,"text":"the experience of living through a great depression,"},{"time":819086,"text":"the experience of living through a world war,"},{"time":821724,"text":"and agonizing whether or not"},{"time":824270,"text":"dropping atomic bombs would be more horrible"},{"time":827307,"text":"than the likely consequences\nof not dropping atomic bombs."},{"time":831420,"text":"Most of our current voters and politicians"},{"time":833696,"text":"have no personal experience of any of those things,"},{"time":836428,"text":"but millions of older Americans do."},{"time":839123,"text":"Unfortunately, all of those terrible situations"},{"time":841774,"text":"could come back."},{"time":843161,"text":"Even if they don't come back,"},{"time":844467,"text":"we have to be able to plan for them"},{"time":846659,"text":"on the basis of the experience of what they were like."},{"time":849470,"text":"Older people have that experience."},{"time":851304,"text":"Younger people don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853357,"text":"The remaining value of older people"},{"time":854877,"text":"that I'll mention involves recognizing that"},{"time":857320,"text":"while there are many things that older people"},{"time":859900,"text":"can no longer do,"},{"time":861506,"text":"there are other things that they can do"},{"time":862995,"text":"better than younger people."},{"time":865090,"text":"A challenge for society is \nto make use of those things"},{"time":867986,"text":"that older people are better at doing."},{"time":870458,"text":"Some abilities, of course, decrease with age."},{"time":873707,"text":"Those include abilities at tasks"},{"time":876345,"text":"requiring physical strength and stamina,"},{"time":879916,"text":"ambition, and the power of novel reasoning"},{"time":883040,"text":"in a circumscribed situation,"},{"time":885465,"text":"such as figuring out the structure of DNA,"},{"time":888053,"text":"best left to scientists under the age of 30."},{"time":891954,"text":"Conversely, valuable attributes"},{"time":893603,"text":"that increase with age include experience,"},{"time":897149,"text":"understanding of people and human relationships,"},{"time":900162,"text":"ability to help other people"},{"time":902453,"text":"without your own ego getting in the way,"},{"time":904881,"text":"and interdisciplinary thinking about large databases,"},{"time":908406,"text":"such as economics and comparative history,"},{"time":911231,"text":"best left to scholars over the age of 60."},{"time":914445,"text":"Hence older people are\nmuch better than younger people"},{"time":916917,"text":"at supervising, administering, advising,"},{"time":920888,"text":"strategizing, teaching, synthesizing,"},{"time":924370,"text":"and devising long-term plans."},{"time":927076,"text":"I've seen this value of older people"},{"time":929096,"text":"with so many of my friends in their 60s,"},{"time":931668,"text":"70s, 80s and 90s,"},{"time":933658,"text":"who are still active as investment managers,"},{"time":936943,"text":"farmers, lawyers and doctors."},{"time":939956,"text":"In short, many traditional societies"},{"time":942086,"text":"make better use of their elderly"},{"time":944199,"text":"and give their elderly more satisfying lives"},{"time":947309,"text":"than we do in modern, big societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950159,"text":"Paradoxically nowadays,"},{"time":952024,"text":"when we have more elderly people than ever before,"},{"time":954950,"text":"living healthier lives and with better medical care"},{"time":957671,"text":"than ever before,"},{"time":959157,"text":"old age is in some respects more miserable"},{"time":961864,"text":"than ever before."},{"time":963631,"text":"The lives of the elderly are widely recognized"},{"time":966053,"text":"as constituting a disaster area"},{"time":968820,"text":"of modern American society."},{"time":971353,"text":"We can surely do better by learning"},{"time":973034,"text":"from the lives of the elderly"},{"time":974909,"text":"in traditional societies."},{"time":976921,"text":"But what's true of the lives of the elderly"},{"time":978863,"text":"in traditional societies"},{"time":980327,"text":"is true of many other features"},{"time":982022,"text":"of traditional societies as well."},{"time":984616,"text":"Of course, I'm not advocating that we all give up"},{"time":987205,"text":"agriculture and metal tools"},{"time":989320,"text":"and return to a hunter-gatherer lifestyle."},{"time":992404,"text":"There are many obvious respects"},{"time":993948,"text":"in which our lives today are far happier"},{"time":996427,"text":"than those in small, traditional societies."},{"time":999489,"text":"To mention just a few examples,"},{"time":1001195,"text":"our lives are longer, materially much richer,"},{"time":1004165,"text":"and less plagued by violence"},{"time":1006448,"text":"than are the lives of people in traditional societies."},{"time":1009676,"text":"But there are also things to be admired"},{"time":1012204,"text":"about people in traditional societies,"},{"time":1014346,"text":"and perhaps to be learned from them."},{"time":1016665,"text":"Their lives are usually socially much richer"},{"time":1019256,"text":"than our lives,"},{"time":1020848,"text":"although materially poorer."},{"time":1023140,"text":"Their children are more self-confident,"},{"time":1026092,"text":"more independent, and more socially skilled"},{"time":1028686,"text":"than are our children."},{"time":1031022,"text":"They think more realistically\nabout dangers than we do."},{"time":1034765,"text":"They almost never die of diabetes, heart disease,"},{"time":1038294,"text":"stroke, and the other noncommunicable diseases"},{"time":1041528,"text":"that will be the causes of death of almost"},{"time":1044040,"text":"all of us in this room today."},{"time":1047126,"text":"Features of the modern lifestyle\npredispose us to those diseases,"},{"time":1051136,"text":"and features of the traditional lifestyle"},{"time":1053370,"text":"protect us against them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1055877,"text":"Those are just some examples of what we can learn"},{"time":1058036,"text":"from traditional societies."},{"time":1060324,"text":"I hope that you will find it as fascinating"},{"time":1062211,"text":"to read about traditional societies"},{"time":1064620,"text":"as I found it to live in those societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067323,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069503,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}